*Developer notes / future plans for SCORECI.SAS:

* Short-term:
* Fix issue with weights=2 or 3 (though not recommended for RD)
* Add sense checks on input parameters;
* Consider adding a wrapper macro for taking individual-level data as input;
* Add qualitative interaction test (Gail-Simon);
* Replace MAXITER & CONVERGE with single precision parameter
* Add MLE estimate for R1 and R0 to the output (pooled estimate for stratified);
* Improve format of output datasets, to mimic standard ODS output tables?;
* Add validation code confirming CMH test equivalence;
* Address relationship to simple chi-squared test;
* Add warning if SKEW=TRUE and p-value non-calculable due to negative discriminant;

* Long-term:
* Standardise code capitalisation & replace tabs with spaces;
* Allow text input for weights, e.g. MH, INV, IVS;
* Add minimum risk weights;
* Add binomial RR and OR;
* Add Poisson RD and RR;
